    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of tree or shrub native to Europe, northwest Africa, and western Asia, used extensively for hedges. It bears white, red or pink blossoms (called 'may'); its fruit, the haw, is a small, round, dark red berry.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
